The paper deals with the logic of knowledge and its interpretation on simplicial complexes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses the use of simplicial complexes in modeling knowledge and belief, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions bisimulation and group notions, which are related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of simplicial action models in dynamics is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses distributed epistemic models, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
